modules.description: Encodes and decodes sequences of integers using a variable-length encoding scheme that optimizes for space efficiency by grouping integers into 63-bit words. It operates on lists and arrays of integers, enabling compact storage and retrieval. This is particularly useful for applications requiring efficient serialization of large datasets, such as indexing or data logging.

Encodes and decodes sequences of integers using a word-bounded scheme optimized for 63-bit integers, with functions to compute encoded length and manipulate bigarrays or I/O channels. Works with sequences of integers and 63-bit bigarrays, supporting direct encoding into or decoding from memory buffers or file channels. Examples include compressing lists into encoded sequences for storage or transmission and reconstructing original values from compressed data.
